name: head of government
desc: head of the executive power of this town, city, municipality, state, country, or other governmental body

name: highway system
desc: system (or specific country specific road type) of which the highway is a part

name: country

name: place of birth

name: place of death
desc: most specific known (e.g. city instead of country, or hospital instead of city) death location of a person, animal or fictional character

name: sex or gender

name: father

name: mother
desc: female parent of the subject. For stepmother, use "stepparent" (P3448)

name: spouse
desc: the subject has the object as their spouse (husband, wife, partner, etc.). Use "unmarried partner" (P451) for non-married companions

name: country of citizenship
desc: the object is a country that recognizes the subject as its citizen

name: continent
desc: continent of which the subject is a part

alias: not a type but is instance of
name: instance of

name: head of state
desc: official with the highest formal authority in a country/state

name: capital
desc: primary city of a country, state or other type of administrative territorial entity

name: official language
desc: language designated as official by this item

name: currency
desc: currency used by item

name: position held

name: child
desc: subject has the object in their family as their offspring son or daughter (independently of their age)

name: shares border with

name: family

name: member of sports team
desc: sports teams or clubs that the subject currently represents or formerly represented

name: screenwriter

name: constellation

name: discoverer or inventor

name: site of astronomical discovery
desc: the place where an astronomical object was discovered (observatory, satellite)

name: ancestral home
desc: place of origin for ancestors of subject

name: educated at
desc: educational institution attended by the subject

name: top-level Internet domain
desc: Internet domain name system top-level code

name: connecting line

name: architect
desc: person or architectural firm that designed this building

name: anthem

name: main regulatory text
desc: text setting the main rules by which the subject is regulated

name: noble title
desc: titles held by the person

name: editor
desc: editor of a compiled work such as a book or academic journal

name: field of work
desc: specialization of a person or organization; see P106 for the occupation

name: member of political party
desc: the political party of which this politician is or has been a member

name: native language
desc: language or languages a person has learned from birth

name: taxon rank

name: occupation

name: employer
desc: person or organization for which the subject works or worked

name: illustrator
desc: person drawing the pictures in a book

name: measured physical quantity
desc: physical property expressed as number multiplied by a unit

name: founded by

name: airline hub
desc: airport that serves as a hub for an airline

name: airline alliance
desc: alliance the airline belongs to

name: league
desc: league in which team or player plays or has played in

name: item operated

name: basic form of government
desc: subject's government

name: publisher
desc: organization or person responsible for publishing books, periodicals, games or software

name: maintained by

name: owned by
desc: owner of the subject

name: regulates (molecular biology)

name: physically interacts with

is in the Indian reserve of
is in the administrative region of
is in the local government area of
is in the rural city of
is in the principal area of

name: has dialect

name: movement

name: genre
desc: a creative work's genre or an artist's field of work (P101). Use main subject (P921) to relate creative works to their topic

name: operator
desc: person or organization that operates the equipment, facility, or service; use country for diplomatic missions

name: named after
desc: entity or event that inspired the subject's name, or namesake (in at least one language)

name: religion
desc: religion of a person, organization or religious building, or associated with this subject

name: IUCN conservation status
desc: conservation status assigned by the International Union for Conservation of Nature

name: imported from
desc: source of this claim's value (use only in References section)

name: architectural style
desc: architectural style of a structure

name: contains administrative territorial entity
desc: (list of) direct subdivisions of an administrative territorial entity

name: followed by

name: killed by

name: headquarters location
desc: specific location where an organization's headquarters is or has been situated

name: cast member
desc: actor performing live for a camera or audience [use "character role" (P453) and/or "name of the character role" (P4633) as qualifiers] [use "voice actor" (P725) for voice-only role]

name: producer
desc: producer(s) of this film or music work (film: not executive producers, associate producers, etc.) [use P272 to refer to the production company]

name: flag
desc: subject's flag

name: award received
desc: award or recognition received by a person, organisation or creative work

name: structure replaced by
desc: the item which replaced this building or structure, at the same geographic location

name: chief executive officer
desc: highest-ranking corporate officer appointed as the CEO within an organization

name: creator
desc: maker of a creative work or other object (where no more specific property exists)

name: parent taxon
desc: closest parent taxon of the taxon in question

name: ethnic group
desc: subject's ethnicity (consensus is that a VERY high standard of proof is needed for this field to be used. In general this means 1) the subject claims it him/herself, or 2) it is widely agreed on by scholars, or 3) is fictional and portrayed as such).

name: performer
desc: performer involved in the performance or the recording of a work

name: manufacturer
desc: manufacturer or producer of this product

name: crosses
desc: obstacle (body of water, road, ...) which this bridge crosses over or this tunnel goes under

name: developer
desc: organisation or person that developed this item

name: series
desc: subject is part of a series, whose sum constitutes the object

name: depicts
desc: depicted entity (see also P921: main subject)

name: endemic to
desc: sole location or habitat type where the taxon lives

name: doctoral advisor
desc: person who supervised the doctorate or PhD thesis of the subject

name: doctoral student
desc: doctoral student(s) of a professor

name: material used
desc: material the subject is made of or derived from

name: location of discovery
desc: where the item was located when discovered

name: sister city

name: main building contractor
desc: the main organization responsible for construction of this structure or building

name: legislative body
desc: legislative body governing this entity; political institution with elected representatives, such as a parliament/legislature or council

name: collection
desc: art, museum or bibliographic collection the subject is part of

name: minor planet group
desc: is in grouping of minor planets according to similar orbital characteristics

name: adjacent station
desc: the stations next to this station, sharing the same line(s)

name: business division
desc: divisions of this organization

name: basin country
desc: country that have drainage to/from or border the body of water

alias: located next to body of water
name: located in or next to body of water
desc: sea, lake or river

name: executive body
desc: branch of government for the daily administration of the state

name: highest judicial authority
desc: supreme judicial body within a country, administrative division, or other organization

name: party chief representative
desc: chief representative of a party in an institution or an administrative unit (use qualifier to identify the party)

name: ISBN-13
desc: identifier for a book (edition), thirteen digit

name: ISNI

name: VIAF ID

name: spectral class
desc: spectral class of an astronomical object

name: inventory number
desc: identifier for a physical object or a set of physical objects in a collection

name: ISO 639-1 code
desc: two-letter identifier for a language or family of languages defined in ISO 639-1 standard

name: ISO 639-2 code
desc: identifier for a language or macrolanguage or language family language, defined in ISO 639-2 standard, 3-letter technical or bibliographical  code

name: ISO 639-3 code
desc: identifier for a language defined in ISO 639-3

name: ISO 639-6 code
desc: identifier for a language per ISO 639-6

name: galaxy morphological type
desc: galaxy morphological classification code

name: taxon name
desc: correct scientific name of a taxon (according to the reference given)

name: GND ID

alias: International Air Transport Association airline designator
name: IATA airline designator
desc: two-character identifier for an airline

alias: International Civil Aviation Organization airline designator
name: ICAO airline designator
desc: three letter identifier for an airline (for airports, see P239)

name: CAS Registry Number
desc: identifier for a chemical compound per CAS Registry

name: EC ID
desc: identifier for a chemical compound per EINECS or ELINCS

name: canonical SMILES
desc: Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry Specification (canonical format)

name: InChI
desc: International Chemical Identifier

name: ISSN
desc: International Standard Serial Number (print or electronic)

name: coat of arms

desc: three-letter identifier for designating airports or cities (for airlines, see P229)

desc: four-character alphanumeric identifier for designating airports (for airlines, see P230)

name: OCLC control number

alias: Library of Congress Name Authority File

name: ULAN ID

name: element symbol
desc: identifier for a chemical element

name: COSPAR ID

name: stated in

name: ticker symbol

name: official residence

name: record label
desc: brand and trademark associated with the marketing of subject music recordings and music videos

name: ATC code

name: production company
desc: company that produced this film, audio or performing arts work

name: chemical formula
desc: description of chemical compound based on element symbols

name: license
desc: license under which this copyrighted work is released

name: location
desc: location of the item, physical object or event is within. In case of an administrative entity use P131. In case of a distinct terrain feature use P706.

name: programming language
desc: the programming language(s) in which the software is developed

name: GOST 7.75–97 code
desc: identifier for a language according to GOST 7.75–97

name: postal code
desc: identifier assigned by postal authorities for the subject area or building

name: writing system

name: vessel class

name: place of publication
desc: geographical place of publication of the edition (use 1st edition when referring to works)

name: station code

name: IETF language tag

name: NDL Auth ID

name: RKDimages

name: Entrez Gene ID

name: UniProt protein ID

name: HGNC gene symbol

name: HGNC ID
desc: identifier for a gene from the HGNC database

name: subsidiary

name: discography

name: software engine

name: quantity symbol

name: seal description

name: located in time zone

name: distribution

name: China administrative division code

name: original network

name: industry

alias: is said to be the same as

name: color

name: input method
